-- Tyco International Names Frank Sklarsky Finance Chief as Coughlin Retires
-- B y   W i l l   D a l e y
-- 2010-10-12T12:35:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-12/tyco-international-names-frank-sklarsky-finance-chief-as-coughlin-retires.html
Tyco International Ltd. , the
world’s largest maker of security systems, named  Frank Sklarsky  as chief financial officer to succeed  Christopher J. Coughlin , who is retiring.  The appointment of Sklarsky, 53, previously the
finance chief of  Eastman Kodak Co. , is effective Dec. 1,
Schaffhausen, Switzerland-based Tyco International said
today in a statement. Coughlin, 58, will advise the company
on certain projects until his retirement in 2011.  Coughlin has been chief financial officer since 2005.
He helped with the spinoff of two units, Tyco Electronics
Ltd. and Covidien Ltd., in 2007 to create three independent
companies, according to the statement.  Sklarsky has been Kodak’s CFO for four years. Before
that, he was finance chief at  ConAgra Foods Inc.   To contact the reporter on this story:
